## TECH STACK

### Backend
- **Language:** Python 3.12
- **Framework:** FastAPI (HTTP + WebSocket)
- **Agent Orchestration:** LangGraph
- **LLM:** Google Gemini Flash (via google-generativeai SDK)
  - Used for: voice conversation reasoning, document entity extraction (vision), agentic validation/correction
  - NOT Claude, NOT OpenAI — we use Gemini throughout
- **Document Parsing:** Docling (text-layer PDFs) + Gemini Flash vision (image/scanned PDFs)
- **Telephony:** Twilio ConversationRelay (voice), Twilio Programmable SMS, Twilio REST API (outbound calls)
- **Tunneling:** ngrok (exposes local WebSocket server to Twilio as wss:// URL)

### Databases
- **PostgreSQL 16** — operational data, intake records, caregiver roster, insurance contracts, reference tables
- **Neo4j 5** — knowledge graph (ICD-10 hierarchy, diagnosis→service→certification mappings, insurance coverage rules, medication interactions)
- **Redis 7** — pipeline state, call state, eligibility caching, follow-up scheduling
- **pgvector** (PostgreSQL extension) — fuzzy matching for insurance plan names, medication names (stretch goal — use pg_trgm first)

### Frontend
- **React 18** with Vite
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling
- **No complex state management** — React useState/useEffect is sufficient for 3 views

### Infrastructure
- **Docker Compose** — all services (PostgreSQL, Neo4j, Redis, FastAPI, React dev server)
- **No cloud deployment** — everything runs locally, ngrok bridges to Twilio

