## ERROR HANDLING — WHAT HAPPENS WHEN THINGS BREAK

### Gemini API Timeout or Error During a Call
- If Gemini doesn't respond within 3 seconds: send filler to Twilio ("One moment please...")
- If Gemini fails after retry: "I apologize, I'm having a technical difficulty. Let me connect you with our coordinator." → end ConversationRelay session
- Never leave the caller in silence for more than 4 seconds

### Database Down During Eligibility Check
- If Neo4j or PostgreSQL is unreachable during a mid-call eligibility check:
  - Don't crash the call
  - Voice Agent says: "I'm unable to check our availability right now, but I've captured all the details. Our coordinator will review and call you back within the hour."
  - Create the intake record with status PENDING_REVIEW
  - Log the database error for debugging

### Twilio WebSocket Disconnection
- ConversationRelay does NOT reconnect automatically
- If WebSocket drops, the call disconnects
- Implement a status callback to detect dropped calls
- Auto-create a follow-up task: "Call back {caller_number} — call dropped during intake"

### Document Pipeline Failure
- If any layer in the pipeline fails, don't lose the work from previous layers
- Save intermediate results to Redis at each layer checkpoint
- Mark the document as FAILED with the failing layer noted
- Allow manual retry from the failed layer, not from scratch

### Frontend Real-Time Updates
- Dashboard polls the backend API every 3 seconds for active referrals and call status
- No WebSocket to frontend — polling is simpler and good enough for hackathon
- Active call data comes from Redis (fast reads) not PostgreSQL

