## TESTING STRATEGY

### Text Mode for Voice Agent
The voice agent has a text-based testing mode that bypasses Twilio entirely:
- `POST /voice/test` — accepts JSON `{"message": "I have a patient referral..."}` and returns the agent's response as text
- Maintains conversation state in memory per test session
- Same LLM logic, same guardrails, same eligibility checks — just no audio
- Use this for rapid iteration before testing with real phone calls

### Database Tests
- Test eligibility queries with known data: "patient in zip 11201 with Medicare Part A needing skilled nursing" → should return ACCEPT
- Test edge cases: expired caregiver certification, unserved zip code, unaccepted insurance → should return DECLINE with correct reason

### Pipeline Tests
- Test with sample PDFs of varying quality
- Verify extraction accuracy against known correct values
- Verify validation catches known errors (invalid ICD codes, impossible dosages)
- Verify confidence scoring aligns with extraction quality

### Live Call Testing
- Only after text mode tests pass
- Use a personal phone to call the Twilio number
- Test each conversation mode: provider, family, self-referral
- Test outbound calls to a personal phone
- Record results and edge cases for demo prep

